    {
      "id": "nS3RTjyprKsfEE6KKPuKp",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 521.8365357711067,
      "y": 2020.5639902277567,
      "width": 1199.419189453125,
      "height": 275,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 80,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b07",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1688264453,
      "version": 969,
      "versionNonce": 248604683,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1781943906129,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "When while copying in clone() function when we say: this.x = x; \nthen primitive DataTypes are copied by Value(Deep Copy), but Complex DataTypes are copied by Reference (Shallow Copy).\n\nSo if we later update that Complex attribute in any 1 object, then all objects using the same reference\nwill also be updated; which may not be an ideal behaviour in some cases.\n\nIf we want Complex attributes to be also copied by value, then we will require to create new instance \nof the Complex attribute (basically Deep Copying).\n\nIn Deep-copying required pointer's address will be different, but in Shallow-Copy pointer's address is same; \nbasically pointing to same Memory-block.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "When while copying in clone() function when we say: this.x = x; \nthen primitive DataTypes are copied by Value(Deep Copy), but Complex DataTypes are copied by Reference (Shallow Copy).\n\nSo if we later update that Complex attribute in any 1 object, then all objects using the same reference\nwill also be updated; which may not be an ideal behaviour in some cases.\n\nIf we want Complex attributes to be also copied by value, then we will require to create new instance \nof the Complex attribute (basically Deep Copying).\n\nIn Deep-copying required pointer's address will be different, but in Shallow-Copy pointer's address is same; \nbasically pointing to same Memory-block.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    }
  ],
